  "verseCount": 18,
  "content": [
    {
      "name": "para",
      "type": "tag",
      "attrs": {
        "style": "p"
      },
      "items": [
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "1",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:1"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "1",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "My brethren, be not many masters, knowing that we shall receive the greater condemnation. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.1",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.1"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "2",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:2"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "2",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For in many things we offend all. If any man offend not in word, the same ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.2",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.2"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.2",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.2"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " a perfect man, ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.2",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.2"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "and",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.2",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.2"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " able also to bridle the whole body. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.2",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.2"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "3",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:3"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "3",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Behold, we put bits in the horsesâ€™ mouths, that they may obey us; and we turn about their whole body. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.3",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.3"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "4",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:4"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "4",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Behold also the ships, which though ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.4",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.4"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "they be",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.4",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.4"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " so great, and ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.4",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.4"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "are",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.4",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.4"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " driven of fierce winds, yet are they turned about with a very small helm, whithersoever the governor listeth. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.4",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.4"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "5",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:5"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "5",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Even so the tongue is a little member, and boasteth great things. Behold, how great a matter a little fire kindleth! ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.5",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.5"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "6",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:6"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "6",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And the tongue ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.6",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.6"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.6",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.6"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " a fire, a world of iniquity: so is the tongue among our members, that it defileth the whole body, and setteth on fire the course of nature; and it is set on fire of hell. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.6",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.6"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "7",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:7"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "7",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For every kind of beasts, and of birds, and of serpents, and of things in the sea, is tamed, and hath been tamed of mankind: ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.7",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.7"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "8",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:8"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "8",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But the tongue can no man tame; ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.8",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.8"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "it is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.8",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.8"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " an unruly evil, full of deadly poison. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.8",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.8"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "9",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:9"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "9",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Therewith bless we God, even the Father; and therewith curse we men, which are made after the similitude of God. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.9",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.9"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "10",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:10"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "10",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Out of the same mouth proceedeth blessing and cursing. My brethren, these things ought not so to be. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.10",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.10"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "11",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:11"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "11",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Doth a fountain send forth at the same place sweet ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.11",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.11"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "water",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.11",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.11"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " and bitter? ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.11",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.11"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "12",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:12"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "12",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Can the fig tree, my brethren, bear olive berries? either a vine, figs? so ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.12",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.12"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "can",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.12",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.12"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " no fountain both yield salt water and fresh. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.12",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.12"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "13",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:13"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "13",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Who ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.13",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.13"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.13",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.13"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " a wise man and endued with knowledge among you? let him shew out of a good conversation his works with meekness of wisdom. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.13",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.13"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "14",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:14"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "14",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But if ye have bitter envying and strife in your hearts, glory not, and lie not against the truth. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.14",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.14"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "15",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:15"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "15",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "This wisdom descendeth not from above, but ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.15",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.15"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.15",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.15"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " earthly, sensual, devilish. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.15",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.15"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "16",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:16"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "16",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For where envying and strife ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.16",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.16"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.16",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.16"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ", there ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.16",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.16"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.16",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.16"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " confusion and every evil work. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.16",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.16"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "17",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:17"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "17",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.17",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.17"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "and",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "JAS.3.17",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "JAS.3.17"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " easy to be intreated, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality, and without hypocrisy. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.17",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.17"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "18",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "JAS 3:18"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "18",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace of them that make peace.",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "JAS.3.18",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "JAS.3.18"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
